'''Pølser''' is the [[Danish language|Danish]] word for [[sausage]] (plural, singular is ''pølse''). Visitors to [[Denmark]] immediately learn this word for '''pølser''' are a very important part of everyday culture in Denmark and an ingredient in the national [[hot dog]].

One is presented with a choice with the Danish hot dog: ''ristet pølse'' or ''kogt pølse''. The first is a [[Bratwurst]] (''ristet'' means "roasted") and the second type is a sausage that has precooked and preprocessed meat that is cooked a second time. 

The most noticeable aspect of ''pølser'' is that in Denmark they often contain a traditional red dye (''rød pølse'') which makes them look bright red.

